President Muhammadu Buhari left Abuja yesterday for his hometown, Daura in Katsina State for a two-day private visit. The president jet’s landed at the Umaru Musa Yar’adua International Airport Katsina at about 4.30pm. He was then received by Governor Aminu Masari who was accompanied by Senators Abu Ibrahim and Umar Ibrahim as well as other top politicians in the state. Thereafter, the president boarded a helicopter to Daura,   about 74 kilometers from Katsina town.